</ul>
<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_Greek_phrases&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> In the <a href="/wiki/Greek_alphabet" title="Greek alphabet">Greek alphabet</a>, the /ps/ sound is rendered by the single letter ψ (<i>psi</i>).</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Horace" title="Horace">Horace</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Ars_Poetica" title="Ars Poetica">Ars Poetica</a></i>, l. 139. Often misquoted as <i>Parturiunt montes, nascitur ridiculus mus</i>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
